(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- Electrolysis: The main topic being studied, understood here as study chemical) Tj
T*
(decomposition using electricity.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: movement of ions) Tj
T*
(and products at the electrodes.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as predicting) Tj
T*
(products from electrolysis of copper sulfate.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example mixing up anode) Tj
T*
(and cathode products.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Electrolysis: movement of ions and products at the) Tj
T*
(electrodes.) Tj
T*
(- Mixing up anode and cathode products.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Electrolysis without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
