T*
(Electrolysis is a valuable part of Chemistry. Students perform better when they) Tj
T*
(understand movement of ions and products at the electrodes, learn from examples such as) Tj
T*
(predicting products from electrolysis of copper sulfate, and deliberately avoid mistakes) Tj
T*
(like mixing up anode and cathode products. Regular practice built around electrode) Tj
T*
(reactions and observations makes the topic easier to remember and apply.) Tj
